Short answer: yes, it’s not active in your config. That rule isn’t enabled anywhere in `biome.jsonc` (and no overrides set it), so a normal `biome lint` won’t report it. When you pass `--only lint/correctness/useExhaustiveDependencies`, you force it on for that run, which is why you see the issue.

If you want it to run by default, add it to the config, e.g.:

```json
{
  "linter": {
    "rules": {
      "correctness": {
        "useExhaustiveDependencies": "error"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

If you want, tell me where you want it (root config vs. app-specific override) and I’ll wire it in.

